Hi Rich, I assume you are rolling out your rules abstraction, which ultimately will generate the JSON definition. The host class definition makes sense. 

If you want to reuse the abstraction in the durable module, I have added an function to create the host alone (instead of runAll), over that you can add your API implementation.

```javascript
host = createHost(); // optional [database object array]
```

Also I have added another function you might find useful. If you have access to the redis instance you can queue a events for rulesets from other hosts (without the ruleset definition).

```javascript
q = d.createQueue('rules'); // optional [database object array]
q.post({id: 1, sid: 2, t: 'deposit'});
q.assert({id: 4, sid: 2, t: 'balance'});
q.retract({id: 4, sid: 2, t: 'balance'});
q.close();
```

