@limpair a couple of comments on the PR:

Regarding your use case, is there any reason you are not using the same driver session to log in and to perform the validation? You could make your script take you to the log in page and make it wait for the 'successful log in' message to appear, then log in manually, and then your script should resume automatically. The example I wrote in the README does exactly that on reddit. Here's the link: https://github.com/tryolabs/requestium/blob/master/README.md#comparison-with-requests--selenium--lxml

If we end up adding this feature though, I think it would be better to just reuse `transfer_driver_cookies_to_session` with a new `external_driver` keyword instead of the new method adding `transfer_local_driver_cookies_to_session`, just to keep things simple.

