@frozen-sky, just talked about this at length with ohemorange. While not initially what you had in mind, how would you feel about uploading certificates during the call to `restart()`? In the non-renew case, you can batch updates and perform them all at once when `restart()` is called.

During renewal, you can access certificate storage using `self.config.live_dir` which will point to `/etc/letsencrypt/live` by default. You can then find certificates there and upload them as needed. I'm not sure how you're storing structuring certificate storage remotely, but this might be very trivial for you if your mimicking the structure of the `/etc/letsencrypt/live` directories. If not, you can walk the directories and determine the domains in the certificates by inspecting them.

Let me know what you think! We definitely want to work with you to make Certbot work for your use case but are a little hesitant to start adding more methods to the plugin API.

